As Myrmidon was already hovering in the air when the slab was tilted,
it did not bother him in the slightest. His only reaction was to
increase his thrust, to push his massive bulk slightly higher in the
air.

He was a sight to behold, hued in deep purple and black armor, his twin
shoulder mounted mortar cannons and an arm mounted cannon mute
testimony to his offensive abilities. His armor was thick and well
crafted as he floated in mid air, boosters flaring from his back. His
head casing was reminiscent of a jungle cat&#39;s head opened in a
perpetual roar, Myrmidon&#39;s optics peering from within the maw past long
toothed fangs.

&quot;HOLD!&quot; Myrmidon&#39;s sonorous voice flowed over the area as he pointed a
clawed finger at Malice. &quot;You bear Decepticon markings, and yet you
attack us!&quot; With an audible click both of his mortar cannons target
Malice and prepare to fire. &quot;Out of respect for your allegiance I give
you one final chance to yield, or the battle begins in earnest.&quot;

OOC: If Hydras chooses to receive the transmissions from Myrmidon, he
would be seeing this as well. 

OOC: Oh, and as Myrmidon had only stepped out of the base and began
hovering, shifting only so much as to allow others to emerge and to
avoid the lava, he is between Malice and the opening to the black
fortress.


Preston
(Myrmidon)

